cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is about conditional image generation, which is a subfield of computer vision. The paper proposes a new architecture for generating images with a desired shape specified by an input normal map. This task involves modeling the appearance of the image via a latent appearance vector. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also involves graphics rendering, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The use of unpaired training samples and the modeling of image appearance using a latent vector suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves generating diverse images, which may also fall under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
